      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WITH IN REASON (4) has been racing well in Victoria, scoring two runs back at Shepparton before leading and sticking on well for a 1.2m second at his latest appearance at Melton. Has recorded a win and two placings in three tries at this distance range. Big chance. KIMCANDO (9) draws for a trail and looks close to a win after placing the last three times she has raced here, racing parked but sticking on for second in a higher-graded race last time. Expect her to pose a serious challenge. MESSERATI (6) could be getting back to form having produced a brave effort for second here last time, working hard to find the front before fighting on well to go under by only 1.8m. SHADES OF MIKI (5) goes up in grade and draws wider but gave a good sight when he led and boxed on for second here last week.",
